:"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/molecular-biology-and-genetics-in-turkey-top-universities.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/molecular-biology-and-genetics-in-turkey-top-universities.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"Molecular Biology and Genetics in Turkey: Top 5 Universities","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/molecular-biology-and-genetics-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/molecular-biology-and-genetics-in-turkey/","name":"Molecular Biology and Genetics in Turkey: 2025 Guide","datePublished":"2025-08-08T16:38:01+03:00","dateModified":"2025-09-04T14:53:42+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/molecular-biology-and-genetics-in-turkey-top-universities.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Molecular Biology and Genetics in Turkey: 2025 Guide","keywords":"Molecular Biology and Genetics","datePublished":"2025-08-08T16:38:01+03:00","dateModified":"2025-09-04T14:53:42+03:00","articleSection":"University and Programs","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Do you want to study Molecular Biology and Genetics in Turkey? Discover the best universities, rankings, salaries and job opportunities!","name":"Molecular Biology and Genetics in Turkey: 2025 Guide","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/molecular-biology-and-genetics-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/molecular-biology-and-genetics-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/molecular-biology-and-genetics-in-turkey-top-universities.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/molecular-biology-and-genetics-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<h2 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">What is the Department of Molecular Biology and Genetics?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, the Department of Molecular Biology and Genetics is a four-year undergraduate program offered at universities, usually under the faculties of Arts and Sciences, Basic Sciences, Engineering or Natural Sciences. This department studies in-depth the structure and function of living organisms at the molecular level and how genetic information is transmitted. Courses include topics such as cell biology, genetics, biochemistry, microbiology, molecular evolution, DNA analysis, genetic engineering and biotechnology. Students acquire both theoretical knowledge and develop practical skills through laboratory applications.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="molecular-biology-and-genetics-education-in-turkey">Molecular Biology and Genetics Education in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, Molecular Biology and Genetics is one of the key fields driving revolutionary developments in biotechnology and health sciences. For students who want to study in this dynamic and rapidly developing field, a deep understanding of genetic sciences and the ability to use this knowledge effectively in research and applied projects starts with the right choice of university. </p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Graduates of the Department of Molecular Biology and Genetics have a wide range of careers; they can assume important roles in the health sector, biotechnology companies, academic research centers, pharmaceutical industry and genetic diagnostic laboratories.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In this guide:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Turkey&#8217;s top <strong>5 Molecular Biology and Genetics universities</strong>,</li>



<li><strong>World and Turkey rankings</strong>,</li>



<li><strong>You will learn about the salaries and career prospects</strong> of Molecular Biology and Genetics graduates.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Let&#8217;s get started!</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can join our <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/studyinturkiye/" data-type="link" data-id="https://www.reddit.com/r/studyinturkiye/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Reddit Community about</a> molecular biology and start a discussion topic to share your experiences or the topics you are curious about.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="5-best-molecular-biology-and-genetics-departments-in-turkey">5 Best Molecular Biology and Genetics Departments in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Among the universities offering Molecular Biology and Genetics education in Turkey, some stand out with their <strong>research projects, academic staff quality and international collaborations</strong>. Here are the 5 best options:</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="1-bogazici-university-istanbul">1. Boğaziçi University &#8211; Istanbul</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Why this school?</strong><br><a href="https://bogazici.edu.tr/tr_TR/Content/Akademik/Lisans_Katalogu/FenEdebiyat_Fakultesi/Molekuler_Biyoloji_ve_Genetik_Bolumu" data-type="link" data-id="https://bogazici.edu.tr/tr_TR/Content/Akademik/Lisans_Katalogu/FenEdebiyat_Fakultesi/Molekuler_Biyoloji_ve_Genetik_Bolumu" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Boğaziçi University,</a> one of the most prestigious English-medium public universities in Turkey. The Molecular Biology and Genetics department is particularly active in cancer research, neuroscience and biotechnology.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Highlights:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Campus in the center of Istanbul with spectacular Bosphorus views</li>



<li>Strong Erasmus+ and exchange programs</li>



<li>Graduates can be accepted to universities such as Harvard, MIT, Cambridge</li>



<li>Research laboratories specializing in molecular biotechnology</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>For International Students:</strong><br>Applications with TOEFL/IELTS are accepted. Quotas are reserved for international students.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="2-bilkent-university-ankara">2. Bilkent University &#8211; Ankara</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Why this school?</strong><br><a href="https://mbg.bilkent.edu.tr/" data-type="link" data-id="https://mbg.bilkent.edu.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bilkent University,</a> is considered one of the best foundation (private) universities in Turkey. It stands out with its modern laboratories and international staff in the field of molecular biology.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Highlights:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Full scholarship programs and dormitory facilities</li>



<li>English education</li>



<li>Advanced laboratory infrastructure and genetic engineering applications</li>



<li>Support for participation in international congresses</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>For International Students:</strong><br>Bilkent offers 100% scholarship to students with a high GPA. The application process is carried out online.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="3-middle-east-technical-university-metu-ankara">3. Middle East Technical University (METU) &#8211; Ankara</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Why this school?</strong><br><a href="https://bio.metu.edu.tr/tr/molekuler-biyoloji-ve-genetik" data-type="link" data-id="https://bio.metu.edu.tr/tr/molekuler-biyoloji-ve-genetik" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ODTÜ (METU),</a> a world-ranked university with a very high number of scientific publications. Molecular Biology and Genetics department is very strong for those who want to turn to fields such as biotechnology, bioinformatics, cancer genetics.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Highlights:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Student exchange agreements with universities in Europe and America</li>



<li>English language education + internship abroad</li>



<li>Chance to take part in TÜBİTAK and European Union projects</li>



<li>Courses with applications in bioinformatics and artificial intelligence</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>For International Students:</strong><br>ODTU accepts applications with TOEFL score and some quotas are reserved only for foreign students.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="4-bahcesehir-university-istanbul">4. Bahçeşehir University &#8211; Istanbul</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Why this school?</strong><br><a href="https://bau.edu.tr/icerik/3307-muhendislik-ve-doga-bilimleri-fakultesi-molekuler-biyoloji-ve-genetik" data-type="link" data-id="https://bau.edu.tr/icerik/3307-muhendislik-ve-doga-bilimleri-fakultesi-molekuler-biyoloji-ve-genetik" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bahçeşehir University (BAU)</a> is a dynamic foundation university that is rapidly developing especially in the fields of health sciences and genetic engineering. The Molecular Biology and Genetics department stands out with its modern laboratory facilities and international collaborations. Offering education in English is a great advantage for foreign students.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Highlights:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>English education</strong> and international academic staff</li>



<li>Highly equipped molecular genetics laboratories at BAU Göztepe Campus</li>



<li><strong>Co-Op system</strong> allows students to do internships in the private sector during their university years</li>



<li>Double degree and summer school opportunities with universities in Europe and the US</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Special Projects and Research Areas:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Experimental studies on genetic diseases</li>



<li>Biotechnology and CRISPR applications</li>



<li>Research groups in neurogenetics and molecular pharmacology</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>For International Students:</strong><br>BAU accepts international students from many countries. Applications can be made with documents such as IELTS and TOEFL. In addition, 25%, 50% and 100% scholarships are offered to successful students.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="5-istanbul-university-istanbul">5. Istanbul University &#8211; Istanbul</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Why this school?</strong><br>Turkey&#8217;s oldest and most established university, <a href="https://molekuler-fen.istanbul.edu.tr/tr/_" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Istanbul University,</a> has a significant academic background in molecular biology and genetics, especially in the fields of <strong>genetic diseases</strong>, <strong>cancer research</strong> and <strong>laboratory techniques</strong>.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Highlights:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Historic campus, central location for transportation</li>



<li>Research opportunities and ease of transfer to graduate school</li>



<li>Turkish language education is predominantly Turkish, but English preparation is available</li>



<li>Practical training in genetic diagnostic laboratories</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>For International Students:</strong><br>Turkish programs can be entered with a TÖMER certificate. English programs are also available.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Check out our <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Road to Study</a> website for more university options.</p>


