<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Question</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the scope of the Molecular Biology and Genetics Department?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It studies the molecular structure of living organisms and genetic information; it covers genetics, biochemistry, and biotechnology.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What do Molecular Biology and Genetics graduates do in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">They work in academia, biotechnology, healthcare, and the pharmaceutical industry; they also engage in genetic counseling and research.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How long does a Molecular Biology and Genetics degree take?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It is a 4-year undergraduate program that includes laboratory work and research projects.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are the job prospects for Molecular Biology and Genetics in Turkey?</h3>



