<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are interested in politics, public administration or international relations, now is the perfect time to study these subjects in Turkey! But which universities are really good at it? </p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Also, universities in Turkey prepare students for the real world with both theoretical courses and field studies. You will learn not only from books but also from Turkey&#8217;s current political atmosphere.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Well, which universities stand out in this regard?</strong></p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="best-political-science-and-public-administration-universities">Best Political Science and Public Administration Universities</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="1-bogazici-university-political-science-and-international-relations">1. Boğaziçi University &#8211; Political Science and International Relations</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Boğaziçi University is known for its academic staff and the opportunity to study in English. Students gain comprehensive knowledge on global policy analysis and Turkey&#8217;s political structure.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Why Choose </strong><br>The international publications of the academic staff, the activity of student societies and exchange programs.</li>



<li><strong>Application Tips:</strong><br>High TOEFL or IELTS score is important. Emphasize a global perspective in your motivational letter.</li>



<li><a href="https://roadtostudy.com/bogazici-universitesi/" data-type="page" data-id="582">For More Information: <strong>Boğaziçi University</strong></a></li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="2-ankara-university-faculty-of-political-sciences-sbf">2. Ankara University &#8211; Faculty of Political Sciences (SBF)</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">One of the oldest political science faculties in Turkey, SBF is known as &#8220;Mülkiye&#8221;. Its graduates have a strong network in the public sector.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
