<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye’de hemşirelik ve ebelik bölümlerinden mezun olan öğrenciler, hem Türkiye’de hem de yurtdışında çok çeşitli alanlarda çalışma imkânı bulabiliyor. Hemşireler; devlet hastaneleri, özel hastaneler, klinikler, yaşlı bakım merkezleri, okullar ve şirketlerin sağlık birimlerinde görev alabiliyorlar. Ebelik mezunları ise doğum klinikleri, kadın doğum servisleri, aile sağlığı merkezleri ve doğum öncesi danışmanlık merkezlerinde çalışabiliyor.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Uluslararası bir öğrenci olarak Türkiye’de okuyup mezun olduktan sonra, Türkiye’de iş başvurusu yapabilir ya da diplomanı denkliğe uygun ülkelerde kullanabilirsin. Özellikle Avrupa ülkeleri ve Orta Doğu’da Türkiye’den alınan sağlık diplomalarına talep oldukça fazla.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ayrıca, klinik görevlerin dışında akademik kariyer, sağlık yönetimi ya da halk sağlığı gibi alanlara yönelmek de mümkün. Kısacası, sağlık eğitimini tamamladıktan sonra yolun yalnızca bir hastane koridorundan geçmek zorunda değil.</p>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="uluslararasi-ogrenciler-icin-basvuru-ve-kabul-sureci">Uluslararası Öğrenciler İçin Başvuru ve Kabul Süreci</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye&#8217;deki üniversitelere başvuru yapmak sandığından daha kolay. İlk olarak, başvuracağın üniversitenin uluslararası ofis sayfasını ziyaret etmen gerekiyor. Çoğu üniversite yılda bir ya da iki defa yabancı öğrenci alımı yapıyor. Başvuru için genelde şu belgeler isteniyor: lise diploması, transkript, pasaport fotokopisi, dil yeterlilik belgesi (eğer İngilizce programsa) ve motivasyon mektubu.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bazı üniversiteler <strong>YÖS (Yabancı Uyruklu Öğrenci Sınavı)</strong> puanı isterken, bazıları lise not ortalamasını yeterli görüyor. İngilizce eğitim veren programlarda TOEFL veya IELTS skoru da gerekebilir.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><br>Güncel başvuru tarihleri ve belgeler için üniversitelerin <strong>uluslararası öğrenci ofisleri</strong> sayfalarını takip etmen önemli: <a class="" href="https://studyinturkiye.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Study in Turkey</a> resmi sayfası da burada sana çok yardımcı olabilir.</p>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="turkiyede-saglik-egitiminin-kalitesi-ve-akreditasyonlar">Türkiye’de Sağlık Eğitiminin Kalitesi ve Akreditasyonlar</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye’de sağlık eğitimi, son yıllarda ciddi bir atılım yaptı. Hemşirelik ve ebelik bölümleri, sadece teorik değil, uygulamalı eğitime de ciddi ağırlık veriyor. Modern simülasyon laboratuvarları, dijital hasta takip sistemleri ve teknoloji destekli ders içerikleri bu alanlarda dikkat çeken unsurlar.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Eğitim programları genellikle <strong>Yükseköğretim Kurulu (YÖK)</strong> tarafından denetleniyor. Aynı zamanda birçok bölüm uluslararası standartlara uygun şekilde <strong>akredite</strong> edilmiş durumda. Örneğin, <strong>FEDEK</strong> ve <strong>Eczacılık Fakülteleri Akreditasyon Kurulu (ECZAK)</strong> gibi kuruluşlar bu alanda kaliteyi denetliyor.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bu sayede Türkiye’de aldığın sağlık diploması, Avrupa’dan Orta Doğu’ya kadar birçok ülkede tanınıyor. Klinik uygulamaların devlet ve özel hastanelerle yapılması da eğitimin sahaya doğrudan entegre olmasını sağlıyor.<br><a class="" href="https://www.fedek.org.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">FEDEK web sitesinde</a> akredite programlara göz atabilirsin.</p>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="hemsirelik-ve-ebelik-okurken-sosyal-hayat-ve-kampus-yasami">Hemşirelik ve Ebelik Okurken Sosyal Hayat ve Kampüs Yaşamı</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Sağlık bölümü okurken yoğun ders programına rağmen kampüs hayatının tadını çıkarmak mümkün. Türkiye&#8217;deki üniversiteler genellikle geniş kampüs alanlarına, öğrenci kulüplerine ve sosyal aktivitelere büyük önem veriyor. Hemşirelik ve ebelik öğrencileri için özel bilim toplulukları, seminerler ve gönüllü sağlık hizmetleri gibi etkinlikler mevcut.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ayrıca, uluslararası öğrenciler için kampüs içinde barınma, yurt dışı değişim programları (Erasmus, Mevlana) ve Türkçe dil kursları da sağlanıyor. Türkiye’de eğitim alırken yeni kültürler tanıyabilir, Türk mutfağından sokak hayatına kadar çok farklı deneyimler yaşayabilirsin.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Mesela İstanbul’da okuyan biri olarak haftasonları tarihi yarımadayı keşfetmek ya da bir Karadeniz turuna çıkmak oldukça ulaşılabilir bir lüks. Sosyal anlamda zengin bir hayat, motivasyonunu yüksek tutmana ciddi katkı sağlıyor.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-04-09T14:52:41Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-02-01T06:49:42Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/nursing-and-midwifery-in-turkey.webp","alt":"Türkiye’de Hemşirelik ve Ebelik: Sağlıkta Geleceğini Kur","title":"nursing-and-midwifery-in-turkey"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'tr' AND "slug" = 'turkiyede-hemsirelik-ve-ebelik' );
UPDATE "ec_posts" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"Forensic Sciences and Criminology in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","description":"A guide for those wishing to study forensic science and criminology in Turkey: the best universities, the application process, and career tips. Discover now!","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Forensic Sciences and Criminology in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","ogDescription":"A guide for those wishing to study forensic science and criminology in Turkey: the best universities, the application process, and career tips. Discover now!","ogImage":"/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/forensic-sciences-and-criminology-in-turkey.webp","twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Forensic Sciences and Criminology in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","twitterDescription":"A guide for those wishing to study forensic science and criminology in Turkey: the best universities, the application process, and career tips. Discover now!","canonicalPath":"/en/forensic-sciences-and-criminology-in-turkey/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiyede-adli-bilimler-ve-kriminoloji/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/forensic-sciences-and-criminology-in-turkey/"},{"hreflang":"fr","href":"/fr/sciences-medico-legales-et-criminologie-en-turquie/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/forensic-sciences-and-criminology-in-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/forensic-sciences-and-criminology-in-turkey.webp","width":"1168","height":"880","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/forensic-sciences-and-criminology-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/forensic-sciences-and-criminology-in-turkey/","name":"Forensic Sciences and Criminology in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-02-27T17:20:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-02-27T17:20:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/forensic-sciences-and-criminology-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Forensic Sciences and Criminology in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","keywords":"Forensic Sciences","datePublished":"2026-02-27T17:20:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-02-27T17:20:00+03:00","articleSection":"University and Programs","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"A guide for those wishing to study forensic science and criminology in Turkey: the best universities, the application process, and career tips. Discover now!","name":"Forensic Sciences and Criminology in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/forensic-sciences-and-criminology-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/forensic-sciences-and-criminology-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/forensic-sciences-and-criminology-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/forensic-sciences-and-criminology-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When we stayed in the library until midnight for a group project at university and realized that we had uploaded the wrong file for a presentation, my friends and I had a panicked laughing fit; it was as if we had misanalyzed a crime scene. Even that chaos sparked my interest in forensic sciences and criminology. Meeting this field in Turkey is like stepping into a puzzle that is much more exciting than that chaos.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-are-forensic-sciences-differences-with-criminology">What are Forensic Sciences? Differences with Criminology</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When we think of forensic sciences, we usually think of CSI scenes, but the reality is a bit more detailed. Forensic sciences enable the investigation of a crime using scientific methods. There are many sub-branches such as DNA analysis, ballistics, toxicology, forensic psychiatry. Criminology is a more theoretical field; it examines the causes of crime, the psychology of the criminal and its effects on society.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Simply put: <br>Forensic sciences try to understand the &#8220;how&#8221; of a crime, while criminology tries to understand the &#8220;why&#8221;. When they work together, they contribute greatly to both crime solving and crime prevention.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are looking for more technical information, you can find detailed resources on <a href="https://www.adlibilimciler.org.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Association of Forensic Sciences</a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="forensic-sciences-and-criminology-education-in-turkey">Forensic Sciences and Criminology Education in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, interest in these fields is increasing. Both state universities and foundation universities have started to offer these programs within their own structures. Generally, these departments are located under the Faculty of Arts and Sciences, Faculty of Law or Faculty of Health Sciences.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Programs usually last 4 years and include theoretical courses as well as practical laboratory work. You gain practical knowledge especially in courses such as forensic toxicology and criminal laboratory techniques. Some universities also offer internship opportunities to students in cooperation with forensic medicine institutions and police departments.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Course content includes the following:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Criminalistics</li>



<li>Techniques of crime scene investigation</li>



<li>Psychology of crime</li>



<li>Judicial ethics and law</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are also English programs for international students, but they are mostly conducted in Turkish.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="best-universities-and-programs-2025-current-list">Best Universities and Programs (2025 Current List)</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are thinking &#8220;Where should I study?&#8221;, here are some of the most prominent universities in forensic sciences and criminology in Turkey as of 2025:</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>1. <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/ankara-universitesi/">Ankara University</a> &#8211; Institute of Forensic Sciences</strong><br>It is one of the oldest institutions in Turkey in this field. It offers forensic sciences education at master&#8217;s and doctoral level. In addition to theoretical knowledge, there are also very strong laboratory facilities.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>2. <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/istanbul-universitesi-2/">Istanb</a><a href="https://roadtostudy.com/istanbul-universitesi/">ul University</a> &#8211; Criminology Master&#8217;s Program</strong><br>The program offers a sociology and law-based approach. It focuses on crime analysis, criminal justice systems and societal impacts.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>3. <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/hacettepe-universitesi/">Hacettepe University</a> &#8211; Forensic Sciences Undergraduate Program</strong><br>One of the few universities offering a 4-year undergraduate program. Graduates can easily find jobs in both public and private sectors.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>4. <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/uskudar-universitesi/">Üsküdar University</a> &#8211; Forensic Sciences and Criminology</strong><br>It draws attention with its special structure combining psychology and forensic sciences. Students have the chance to practice directly in forensic medicine and psychology laboratories.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When choosing a program, I recommend you pay attention to the following:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Language of instruction (Turkish or English?)</li>



<li>Number of applied courses</li>



<li>Cooperating institutions (Forensic Medicine Institute, Police, etc.)</li>



<li>Graduates&#8217; employment rate</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you want to enrich the content, you can review the program details on <a href="https://yokatlas.yok.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YÖK Atlas</a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="entry-requirements-and-application-process">Entry Requirements and Application Process</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you want to apply to Forensic Science or Criminology programs in Turkey, the process is generally similar to other undergraduate programs. However, there are some critical points. It is especially important that the documents are complete and on time. I forgot the English translation of the transcript in my first application, I struggled for days.</p>


<h3 id="lisans-programi-basvurulari" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Applications for Undergraduate Program</strong></h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applications at undergraduate level are generally open to <strong>international diplomas recognized by YÖK</strong>. If you did not attend high school in Turkey, here are the documents you need to have:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>High school diploma (and notarized Turkish translation)</li>



<li>Transcript</li>



<li>Passport photocopy</li>



<li>Turkish proficiency certificate (for some universities)</li>



<li>Foreign national student exam (YÖS) results or international exams such as SAT/ACT</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applications usually open in <strong>June-July</strong> every year. However, if you work with <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Road to Study application consultancy</a>, you can manage this process much more easily and correctly. They are especially helpful in terms of document compliance and university selection.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="yuksek-lisans-ve-doktora-programlari"><strong>Master&#8217;s and Doctoral Programs</strong></h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you completed your bachelor&#8217;s degree in another country and want to pursue a master&#8217;s degree in Turkey, you will need the following documents:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Bachelor&#8217;s degree diploma and transcript (English or Turkish)</li>



<li>Letter of intent (Your motivation is very important, you must write it yourself)</li>



<li>Letters of reference</li>



<li>Academic proficiency exam (ALES or GRE)</li>



<li>Language certificate (TOEFL, IELTS or Turkish proficiency)</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applications are usually accepted through the university&#8217;s own website. The terms of each program can vary, so it&#8217;s good to start researching early.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="career-opportunities-and-job-opportunities-for-graduates">Career Opportunities and Job Opportunities for Graduates</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">What can you do when you finish this department? Answer: Quite a lot! There are various career paths for graduates in Turkey and internationally. Some graduates even work in private criminal laboratories, while others join the police departments directly.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="kamu-sektoru"><strong>Public Sector</strong></h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Forensic science graduates can work in institutions such as the Forensic Medicine Institute, <a href="https://www.egm.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">General Directorate of Security</a> and <a href="https://www.adalet.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ministry of Justice</a> in Turkey. There is a serious need for personnel especially in the fields of crime scene investigation, criminal laboratory and forensic medicine.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Criminology graduates can work in <strong><a href="https://cte.adalet.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">prison enforcement agencies</a></strong>, <strong>rehabilitation centers</strong> and <strong>social services</strong>. Students who double major in psychology or sociology have more advantages.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="ozel-sektor-ve-ternational-field"><strong>Private Sector and the International Field</strong></h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Private criminal laboratories, forensic accounting companies, cyber security firms are also very attractive. It is even possible to apply for a job through the Europass system if you have received education in this field in European countries.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For graduates who want to work abroad, internship and job opportunities are also offered in international organizations such as <a>Europol</a> and <a>Interpol</a>. To apply to these institutions, a master&#8217;s degree and a foreign language (especially English, French) are generally required.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="why-should-you-study-forensic-sciences-and-criminology-in-turkey-personal-observations">Why Should You Study Forensic Sciences and Criminology in Turkey? Personal Observations</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">OK, Turkey offers education in this field, but if you are asking &#8220;why should I study here?&#8221;, let me tell you a few things from my own experience. Turkey is a very special bridge between East and West, both culturally and academically.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">I visited a forensic medicine center in Istanbul; it was really equipped to international standards. Students used to go to the incident one-on-one and prepare a report. I think this practice-oriented system is very valuable in terms of reinforcing theoretical knowledge.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Also the cost of living is much more affordable than in Europe. A friend of mine is studying forensic sciences in Germany, paying 700 euros just for rent. I can get the same education here for a quarter of the price. There is a significant difference in food, transportation and accommodation.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Cultural diversity and hospitality are also very different. Being a student in Turkey is not only an academic experience, but also a <strong>life experience</strong>. Every day you learn something new, taste a new food, make a new friend.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-02-27T14:20:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-02-01T06:51:25Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/forensic-sciences-and-criminology-in-turkey.webp","alt":"Forensic Sciences and Criminology in Turkey","title":"forensic-sciences-and-criminology-in-turkey"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'forensic-sciences-and-criminology-in-turkey';
